name: Green Camp Bali
address: Banjar Saren, Jl. Raya, Sibang Kaja, Kec. Abiansemal, Kabupaten Badung, Bali 80352, Indonesia
review 1: What an awesome place. Kids were learning and experience a lot of new stuff relate to nature and ecosystem conservation. As an adult, i enjoyed the activities too. Super friendly, helpful and professional facilitators are ready to guide and help you. Amazing facilities, excellent programs, healthy and delicious food and unforgettable experience. Totally worth it!!
review 2:
Nothing good here for learning in this new world except insect bites and sleepless nights. You could get them for free.
Lousy old bus that they claimed envoronm friendly what a tourist trap.
Cellphone not allowed (maybe 10-15min a day) worse than prison.
I dont understand why did the school send them here. Most parents were uninformed. And they made it mandatory for their academic  grades.
The children were motivated to be excited for this trip by their marketing pictures.

I hope this review helps. And most parents could save money in these tough times.

Bbs parent
review 3:
It had everything I was looking for when I signed up for green camp.
- Quality time with my child
- getting to know other parents
- exposing my city kid to more nature and less screen time.

Mosquitoes are a given but it‚Äôs survivable and after a week, you won‚Äôt remember them. But you will remember green camp for a long time.

Also book yourself a nice hotel and dinner after you check out!
review 4: Awesome green camp!! Had so much fun family Bonding activities!! Highly recommended for family with young children as well to appreciate nature and balinese culture!!
review 5:
Very cool place... an educational place that can provide inspiration for anyone.

Unique bamboo building, super inspiring toilet. Everything returns to nature.

Schools, offices and anyone need to study here to be applied in the place where they live

name: Warung Demung
address: Banjar Lambing, Jl. Raya Sibang Kaja, Sibang Kaja, Kec. Abiansemal, Kabupaten Badung, Bali 80352, Indonesia
review 1: i bought ayam saos padang and sayur kangkung here. the taste was ok, i got sayur kangkung in big portion (too much for me.)
review 2: Surprisingly good! I actually love to order tempe mendoan. It looks like a regular fried tempe tbh instead of mendoan but it's tasty. We love the sapo tahu & ayam geprek. Will try other foods later;D
review 3: What a delicious house! Thanks to you, I've enjoyed my trip :) xoxo
review 4: Warung Demung always delivers great food with a smile. The Tempe Mendoan and Sop Tofu go well with grilled Gurami and Ayam Kampung. We will be back for another meal. Thankyou Warung Demung.
review 5: Amazing and tasty food. Good service and has vegan options.

name: Babi Guling Men Doglag
address: Jl. Raya Sibang Kaja No.3, Sibang Kaja, Kec. Abiansemal, Kabupaten Badung, Bali 80352, Indonesia
review 1:
On my way to Ubud I have an old habit. It's Babi Guling! I must have tried a dozen of them over the years... Babi Guling Men Doglag is one of my favorites. Nice portion of Nasi Campur Babi Guling + Kuah for 35k. Really tasty, spicy but not too much, it's a Balinese delicacy.
Plus Pak is really nice.
You'll pay double that in Ubud for something generally cold, tasteless, in a warung dedicated to tourists.
Try it here, you won't regret it ü§§ü§§

name: Buchadi Kombucha
address: Jl. Cemp. 1 No.11, Banjar Lambing, Sibang Kaja, Kec. Abiansemal, Kabupaten Badung, Bali 80352, Indonesia
review 1: This place seems to be owned and managed by one passionate guy who knows his stuff and is very kind and welcoming to the customer. I came at a random time and he opened shop for me, gave me free testers of his products and explained me many things while talking about kombucha. The kombucha itself is with very interesting flavour combinations as wel as nice and fizzy. Overall great experience.

review 1: Very clean. Good customer service. Good food with reasonable price. Definitely will be my new go to place whenever i visit this area/otw to ubud/sangeh/on my way back to umalas. This is a great spot!!!

name: Student Village - Bamboo Village
address: C6M8+8CW, Jl. Raya, Sibang Kaja, Kec. Abiansemal, Kabupaten Badung, Bali 80352, Indonesia
review 1:
Warmly welcomed and they are extremely polite and professional!
Little further away from tourism and such, but it's easy to get a Uber, Grab or hire a local. They can also get you a motorbike.
If you're lucky you could get a warm shower out in the rain ;-)
review 2: A lovely place affiliated with Green School (located across the river). Provides: educational workshops, housing for GS students from grades 6-11, and bamboo houses you can rent.
review 3:
This is a great place to expose students to.
In this age when children are so into their gadgets, it's wonderful to give them a break and return to nature.
review 4: A nice place for finding something new although the entrance ticket is high.
review 5: great place, great villa, very natural

name: The Milennium Bridge
address: Jalan Melati No.10, Sibang Kaja, Abiansemal, Sibang Kaja, Kec. Abiansemal, Kabupaten Badung, Bali 80352, Indonesia
review 1:
Bridge is not publicly accessible. It is part of some school. We didn't know that and walked in. There was no sing or anything. Security was nice and gave us no trouble but told us that place is closed and they do tours only on Thursdays for 200k IDR per person. Bridge itself was nice.
We found this place on atlas obscura.
